>> Good evening, developers, and

00:00:09.566 --> 00:00:13.376
welcome to the 2019 Apple Design

00:00:13.456 --> 00:00:13.666
Awards.

00:00:14.116 --> 00:00:16.065
Now, here's your host, Senior

00:00:16.146 --> 00:00:18.286
Director of Evangelism, John

00:00:18.526 --> 00:00:18.906
Geleynse.

00:00:19.516 --> 00:00:25.836
[ Music ]

00:00:26.336 --> 00:00:28.886
>> Hello. Well, hello, and

00:00:28.886 --> 00:00:30.806
welcome to another Apple Design

00:00:30.806 --> 00:00:31.176
Awards.

00:00:31.746 --> 00:00:32.936
Thanks for joining us this

00:00:32.936 --> 00:00:34.606
afternoon, especially after a

00:00:34.606 --> 00:00:36.756
long, but exciting day.

00:00:36.756 --> 00:00:39.116
And I just want to particularly

00:00:39.116 --> 00:00:40.716
thank all of you who have joined

00:00:40.716 --> 00:00:43.016
us from around the world online

00:00:43.316 --> 00:00:44.296
on the live stream for the

00:00:44.296 --> 00:00:45.246
ceremony right now.

00:00:45.386 --> 00:00:47.266
We've got a huge group.

00:00:50.136 --> 00:00:52.046
You know, it's great for us to

00:00:52.046 --> 00:00:53.626
join as a community, and gather

00:00:53.626 --> 00:00:55.856
like this to take a few moments

00:00:56.476 --> 00:00:58.686
to celebrate and acknowledge

00:00:58.966 --> 00:01:00.356
excellence in innovation and

00:01:00.356 --> 00:01:00.756
design.

00:01:01.996 --> 00:01:03.386
Because at Apple, we've been

00:01:03.386 --> 00:01:05.306
awarding excellent design for

00:01:05.306 --> 00:01:06.666
more than two decades now.

00:01:08.146 --> 00:01:09.886
What started originally as the

00:01:09.886 --> 00:01:11.556
Apple Human Interface Design

00:01:11.556 --> 00:01:13.196
Excellence Awards, or HIDE

00:01:13.196 --> 00:01:15.396
Awards for short, was renamed a

00:01:15.396 --> 00:01:17.606
few years later to what is now

00:01:17.606 --> 00:01:19.456
known as the Apple Design

00:01:19.456 --> 00:01:20.000
Awards.

00:01:22.116 --> 00:01:24.676
You know, the world around us is

00:01:24.856 --> 00:01:27.856
stunningly beautiful, and as

00:01:27.856 --> 00:01:29.616
humans, we're attracted to

00:01:29.616 --> 00:01:32.436
beautiful things, and to

00:01:32.436 --> 00:01:33.476
incredible designs.

00:01:34.796 --> 00:01:36.806
We're drawn to these things, and

00:01:36.806 --> 00:01:38.496
we respond to them deeply.

00:01:39.176 --> 00:01:42.056
And at Apple, we believe the

00:01:42.056 --> 00:01:43.466
true -- the beauty -- that

00:01:43.466 --> 00:01:44.916
beautiful design is both

00:01:44.916 --> 00:01:47.936
appearance and function, and

00:01:47.936 --> 00:01:49.796
something that works well with

00:01:49.796 --> 00:01:51.416
each component deeply

00:01:51.416 --> 00:01:53.046
considered, and each aspect

00:01:53.356 --> 00:01:55.326
carefully crafted -- that that

00:01:55.326 --> 00:01:56.986
can be profoundly beautiful.

00:01:58.366 --> 00:01:59.936
And so, simply judging something

00:01:59.936 --> 00:02:02.146
by how it looks isn't enough.

00:02:03.256 --> 00:02:04.356
It's how it works.

00:02:04.896 --> 00:02:06.746
It has to work as beautifully as

00:02:06.746 --> 00:02:10.425
it looks, and great design

00:02:10.696 --> 00:02:12.126
reflects the broader definition

00:02:12.126 --> 00:02:12.946
of beauty.

00:02:13.196 --> 00:02:15.486
And it runs deeper than the

00:02:15.486 --> 00:02:16.066
interface.

00:02:16.496 --> 00:02:18.136
It's coherent, and it's

00:02:18.136 --> 00:02:19.116
cohesive.

00:02:19.116 --> 00:02:21.446
And it helps us to engage with

00:02:21.446 --> 00:02:23.276
each other in new, and

00:02:23.276 --> 00:02:25.176
innovative, and life-enhancing

00:02:25.176 --> 00:02:27.556
ways, and like compelling

00:02:27.556 --> 00:02:29.966
beauty, great design draws us

00:02:30.036 --> 00:02:30.736
in.

00:02:31.186 --> 00:02:33.836
And the Apple Design Awards have

00:02:33.836 --> 00:02:35.306
always been about this --

00:02:36.076 --> 00:02:38.026
recognizing great design, and

00:02:38.026 --> 00:02:40.526
then celebrating the developers

00:02:40.526 --> 00:02:42.486
who positively impact everyone

00:02:42.486 --> 00:02:44.226
else, and real people with the

00:02:44.226 --> 00:02:46.196
things that they create, the

00:02:46.296 --> 00:02:47.546
things that you create.

00:02:49.096 --> 00:02:51.116
Now, we select our winners each

00:02:51.116 --> 00:02:53.476
year by evaluating them in

00:02:53.476 --> 00:02:56.000
basically three key areas.

00:02:57.326 --> 00:02:58.616
The first area is design.

00:03:00.136 --> 00:03:01.836
We're looking for apps that are

00:03:02.176 --> 00:03:03.586
-- that have strong visual

00:03:03.586 --> 00:03:06.566
design, that are efficient and

00:03:06.566 --> 00:03:09.366
easy to use, that have great

00:03:09.366 --> 00:03:12.336
game play, that have attention

00:03:12.336 --> 00:03:15.136
to detail and polish, that are

00:03:15.136 --> 00:03:16.636
internally coherent.

00:03:17.136 --> 00:03:19.876
On the technology front, we're

00:03:19.876 --> 00:03:22.486
evaluating technology usage, and

00:03:22.486 --> 00:03:23.636
so we're looking for apps that

00:03:23.636 --> 00:03:25.096
are fast and responsive.

00:03:25.806 --> 00:03:27.216
We're looking for apps that take

00:03:27.366 --> 00:03:28.946
full advantage of all of the

00:03:28.946 --> 00:03:30.186
capabilities of our latest

00:03:30.216 --> 00:03:32.506
devices, and we're looking for

00:03:32.506 --> 00:03:34.926
apps that use the latest Apple

00:03:34.926 --> 00:03:37.686
technologies to do really great

00:03:37.736 --> 00:03:38.466
new things.

00:03:39.166 --> 00:03:41.836
And on the innovation front,

00:03:42.656 --> 00:03:44.216
we're looking for brilliance.

00:03:45.076 --> 00:03:47.306
We're looking for new ideas.

00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:50.296
We're looking for uniqueness,

00:03:51.556 --> 00:03:54.476
platform differentiation, and

00:03:54.546 --> 00:03:55.606
things that just weren't

00:03:55.606 --> 00:03:56.666
possible before.

00:03:57.306 --> 00:03:59.996
And the developers of our

00:03:59.996 --> 00:04:02.116
winning apps this evening have

00:04:02.116 --> 00:04:04.276
done an outstanding job, and

00:04:04.276 --> 00:04:06.086
outstanding work in these three

00:04:06.086 --> 00:04:09.106
areas, and more, and we want to

00:04:09.106 --> 00:04:10.096
honor that work.

00:04:10.896 --> 00:04:12.266
We want to acknowledge the

00:04:12.266 --> 00:04:14.766
distinct joy and the challenges

00:04:14.836 --> 00:04:16.466
of the app creation process that

00:04:16.466 --> 00:04:17.706
we're all so familiar with.

00:04:19.096 --> 00:04:20.426
We want to honor the endless

00:04:20.426 --> 00:04:22.926
hours, the late nights, and the

00:04:22.926 --> 00:04:24.886
dedication that goes into the

00:04:24.936 --> 00:04:26.006
pursuit of excellence.

00:04:26.736 --> 00:04:29.706
We want to recognize the

00:04:29.806 --> 00:04:32.196
dead-ends, and the frustration,

00:04:32.476 --> 00:04:34.196
and the exhaustion sometimes

00:04:34.676 --> 00:04:37.626
that often goes unseen, and

00:04:37.626 --> 00:04:38.786
we're all familiar with that.

00:04:39.956 --> 00:04:41.066
And we want to honor the

00:04:41.066 --> 00:04:43.086
unconventional thinking, the

00:04:43.086 --> 00:04:45.756
creativity, and the new ideas

00:04:46.066 --> 00:04:48.176
that lead to breakthroughs and

00:04:48.176 --> 00:04:49.496
innovative solutions.

00:04:50.046 --> 00:04:51.216
So let's get started.

00:04:52.696 --> 00:04:53.936
Winners tonight are going to win

00:04:53.936 --> 00:04:55.956
some pretty great -- some pretty

00:04:55.956 --> 00:04:58.846
amazing prizes, and each prize

00:04:58.846 --> 00:05:02.206
package includes a 512 gigabyte

00:05:02.206 --> 00:05:04.446
iPhone XS with a set of AirPods,

00:05:06.056 --> 00:05:09.456
a 512 gigabyte 12.9-inch iPad

00:05:09.566 --> 00:05:11.466
Pro with Apple Pencil 2,

00:05:11.946 --> 00:05:18.646
a 64 gigabyte 4K Apple TV, an

00:05:19.786 --> 00:05:22.346
Apple Watch Series 4,

00:05:22.926 --> 00:05:27.066
a top-of-the-line MacBook Pro,

00:05:27.486 --> 00:05:30.786
and a fully-loaded iMac Pro.

00:05:31.916 --> 00:05:33.306
In addition --

00:05:36.346 --> 00:05:37.606
in addition -- and this is what

00:05:37.606 --> 00:05:41.136
all of you want -- each winner

00:05:41.136 --> 00:05:42.786
will -- each winning develop --

00:05:42.786 --> 00:05:43.946
each winning app will be

00:05:43.946 --> 00:05:45.246
highlighted on the App Store,

00:05:45.246 --> 00:05:47.066
similar to what we did last year

00:05:47.066 --> 00:05:48.406
on the Today tab for the Apple

00:05:48.406 --> 00:05:49.776
Design Award winners, and what

00:05:49.776 --> 00:05:51.016
we did throughout the year

00:05:51.226 --> 00:05:52.506
following the ceremony.

00:05:52.896 --> 00:05:53.906
So this year's winners will be

00:05:53.906 --> 00:05:55.456
highlighted in prominent ways on

00:05:55.456 --> 00:05:56.246
the App Stores.

00:05:57.196 --> 00:05:58.546
And lastly, each winner will

00:05:58.546 --> 00:06:00.076
take home one of the coveted

00:06:00.076 --> 00:06:01.636
Apple Design Award trophies,

00:06:04.106 --> 00:06:06.776
except that we thought it was

00:06:06.856 --> 00:06:08.016
time for a refresh.

00:06:08.416 --> 00:06:11.476
And so, we have a completely new

00:06:11.476 --> 00:06:13.466
trophy this year, redesigned

00:06:13.596 --> 00:06:15.036
from the Apple Design Team.

00:06:15.496 --> 00:06:17.146
It retains the integrity and

00:06:17.146 --> 00:06:18.596
recognizable qualities of the

00:06:18.596 --> 00:06:21.166
original award, but reinterprets

00:06:21.166 --> 00:06:22.786
these with the qualities of our

00:06:22.786 --> 00:06:23.706
latest products.

00:06:24.116 --> 00:06:26.596
It's made out of 100% recycled

00:06:26.596 --> 00:06:27.686
aluminum, and featured a

00:06:27.686 --> 00:06:29.986
mirror-finished stainless steel

00:06:29.986 --> 00:06:31.766
Apple logo inlay.

00:06:32.486 --> 00:06:33.966
It's pretty sweet, if you ask

00:06:33.966 --> 00:06:34.330
me.

00:06:37.136 --> 00:06:37.326
All right.

00:06:38.156 --> 00:06:41.326
So we have nine -- we have nine

00:06:41.326 --> 00:06:43.546
winners today, and each winner

00:06:43.546 --> 00:06:45.336
will be announced and demoed by

00:06:45.336 --> 00:06:46.706
a colleague -- by colleagues of

00:06:46.706 --> 00:06:48.576
mine from the Apple -- from the

00:06:48.576 --> 00:06:49.446
-- from Apple's World Wide

00:06:49.446 --> 00:06:50.896
Developer Relations Team.

00:06:51.196 --> 00:06:52.706
Now, a little bit differently

00:06:52.706 --> 00:06:54.316
than other years -- if we

00:06:54.316 --> 00:06:55.846
announce your app, if we

00:06:55.846 --> 00:06:57.566
announce you as a winner, please

00:06:57.606 --> 00:06:59.596
stay in your seat because we're

00:06:59.596 --> 00:07:00.726
going to first talk about your

00:07:00.726 --> 00:07:02.456
app, and explain it to the

00:07:02.456 --> 00:07:03.296
community.

00:07:03.476 --> 00:07:04.816
And we're going to demo it, and

00:07:04.816 --> 00:07:06.436
when we've completed the demo,

00:07:06.436 --> 00:07:07.616
we're going to call you forward

00:07:07.616 --> 00:07:09.236
on stage, and ask that you'd

00:07:09.236 --> 00:07:10.576
come up on stage using these

00:07:10.576 --> 00:07:13.506
stairs here at this location.

00:07:14.016 --> 00:07:16.966
So, let's find out who the

00:07:17.056 --> 00:07:18.036
winners are.

00:07:18.786 --> 00:07:21.026
To present our first winners,

00:07:21.026 --> 00:07:21.866
I'd like to invite my

00:07:21.866 --> 00:07:24.116
colleagues, Si Ching and Oscar

00:07:24.116 --> 00:07:24.536
on stage.

00:07:25.516 --> 00:07:31.126
[ Music ]

00:07:31.626 --> 00:07:32.076
>> Thanks, John.

00:07:33.146 --> 00:07:34.906
For our first award today, we

00:07:34.906 --> 00:07:36.656
have a gorgeous platform game

00:07:37.036 --> 00:07:38.566
designed for the mobile screen

00:07:38.696 --> 00:07:39.696
from the ground up.

00:07:40.056 --> 00:07:41.676
It's optimized for the portrait

00:07:41.676 --> 00:07:43.506
orientation with simple

00:07:43.506 --> 00:07:44.636
drag-and-release controls.

00:07:45.286 --> 00:07:46.996
Oscar and I had so much fun with

00:07:46.996 --> 00:07:48.486
this game, and we can't wait to

00:07:48.486 --> 00:07:49.066
show it to you.

00:07:49.826 --> 00:07:53.066
The first award goes to Ordia by

00:07:53.066 --> 00:07:53.486
Loju.

00:07:54.516 --> 00:08:04.086
[ Applause ]

00:08:04.586 --> 00:08:06.566
Okay, let's get the demo up.

00:08:08.266 --> 00:08:09.896
Okay, Oscar, let's take this

00:08:09.896 --> 00:08:11.336
game for a spin.

00:08:11.786 --> 00:08:13.996
Ordia tells the story of a first

00:08:14.086 --> 00:08:16.066
life form emerging from this

00:08:16.216 --> 00:08:18.466
gooey primordial soup, and then

00:08:18.466 --> 00:08:20.406
goes on a precarious trip to

00:08:20.406 --> 00:08:21.786
start its journey as a living

00:08:21.786 --> 00:08:22.126
being.

00:08:22.126 --> 00:08:23.986
It needs to jump through caves,

00:08:24.236 --> 00:08:26.306
gather nutrition, while also

00:08:26.306 --> 00:08:27.686
avoid being eaten or killed.

00:08:28.856 --> 00:08:30.966
Ordia has its amazingly-rich and

00:08:31.016 --> 00:08:33.015
vibrant design style, a lovely

00:08:33.186 --> 00:08:34.785
blobbiness and bounciness

00:08:34.785 --> 00:08:36.155
throughout -- not just with the

00:08:36.155 --> 00:08:37.716
visuals, but also the sound

00:08:37.716 --> 00:08:37.976
design.

00:08:38.515 --> 00:08:42.296
[ Game Sounds ]

00:08:42.796 --> 00:08:44.676
What we love about this game is

00:08:44.676 --> 00:08:46.296
that it's intuitive enough so

00:08:46.296 --> 00:08:48.376
you simply start playing, and it

00:08:48.376 --> 00:08:50.076
introduces rules and challenges

00:08:50.076 --> 00:08:51.916
gradually as you go through the

00:08:52.086 --> 00:08:53.176
levels.

00:08:53.176 --> 00:08:54.986
It uses colors to communicate

00:08:54.986 --> 00:08:55.936
the roles of each element.

00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:57.416
Green and yellow things are

00:08:57.476 --> 00:08:59.146
friendly, while pink things must

00:08:59.176 --> 00:08:59.726
be avoided.

00:08:59.726 --> 00:09:02.316
It also leverages our Taptic

00:09:02.316 --> 00:09:04.086
Engine just the right amount, so

00:09:04.216 --> 00:09:05.796
you get this subtle and

00:09:05.796 --> 00:09:06.886
satisfying feedback while you

00:09:06.886 --> 00:09:06.976
play.

00:09:11.086 --> 00:09:12.616
Ordia has three universes.

00:09:13.176 --> 00:09:15.906
They are immersive, consistent,

00:09:16.256 --> 00:09:17.786
yet also distinct from each

00:09:17.786 --> 00:09:19.626
other, with carefully balanced

00:09:19.626 --> 00:09:21.176
color palette, different game

00:09:21.176 --> 00:09:22.446
elements, and soundtracks.

00:09:23.426 --> 00:09:24.596
Now, let's have a look at the

00:09:24.636 --> 00:09:25.296
jungle universe.

00:09:25.296 --> 00:09:26.996
This is actually a really tough

00:09:26.996 --> 00:09:27.406
level.

00:09:27.476 --> 00:09:28.616
I've never been able to go

00:09:28.616 --> 00:09:29.906
through without dying, so good

00:09:29.906 --> 00:09:30.500
luck, Oscar.

00:09:33.566 --> 00:09:35.246
I love the pacing of this game.

00:09:35.806 --> 00:09:37.106
The challenges alternate

00:09:37.296 --> 00:09:38.716
smoothly between speed, timing,

00:09:38.826 --> 00:09:42.136
and accuracy, while also offers

00:09:42.166 --> 00:09:43.496
you these little resting pods,

00:09:43.846 --> 00:09:45.366
where your Ordia can regenerate

00:09:45.366 --> 00:09:46.826
if it dies, so you can breathe a

00:09:46.826 --> 00:09:47.156
little.

00:09:47.626 --> 00:09:49.706
The balance between difficulty

00:09:49.856 --> 00:09:51.546
and satisfaction is very well

00:09:51.546 --> 00:09:53.136
managed, so you just feel like

00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:54.716
you have to play one more level.

00:09:57.176 --> 00:09:59.106
Ordia caters for accessibility

00:09:59.106 --> 00:10:00.116
with great care.

00:10:00.526 --> 00:10:02.366
Its colorblindness mode has even

00:10:02.526 --> 00:10:03.786
been tested on monochrome.

00:10:03.786 --> 00:10:06.456
Now, what if you want to do a

00:10:06.456 --> 00:10:08.256
challenge on a level where you

00:10:08.256 --> 00:10:10.176
catch every single nutrition, or

00:10:10.176 --> 00:10:11.546
race for your fastest completion

00:10:11.546 --> 00:10:11.796
time?

00:10:12.346 --> 00:10:13.276
No problem.

00:10:13.276 --> 00:10:14.846
You can also play on an iPad

00:10:14.846 --> 00:10:15.836
with a much larger screen.

00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:18.016
The game automatically syncs

00:10:18.016 --> 00:10:19.136
your progress via iCloud.

00:10:19.226 --> 00:10:23.546
Loju is the creator of Ordia, a

00:10:23.546 --> 00:10:25.236
very small and talented game

00:10:25.316 --> 00:10:26.556
studio based in London.

00:10:27.056 --> 00:10:29.256
They spent two years building

00:10:29.256 --> 00:10:30.756
this game, and have just

00:10:30.756 --> 00:10:32.336
launched it a month ago.

00:10:32.646 --> 00:10:33.486
Please, go ahead.

00:10:33.936 --> 00:10:35.006
Download it today and have a

00:10:35.096 --> 00:10:35.336
play.

00:10:35.596 --> 00:10:37.176
I'm sure you'll get so much

00:10:37.176 --> 00:10:38.696
inspiration from it.

00:10:38.746 --> 00:10:41.946
And now, let's welcome Team Loju

00:10:41.946 --> 00:10:42.516
to the stage.

00:10:43.066 --> 00:10:43.556
Congratulations.

00:10:44.516 --> 00:11:21.516
[ Music and Singing ]

00:11:22.516 --> 00:11:27.736
[ Applause ]

00:11:28.236 --> 00:11:29.056
>> That's a fun game.

