blank page.

00:12:03.546 --> 00:12:04.746
When inspiration strikes, you

00:12:04.746 --> 00:12:06.596
grab a pen, and let the ideas

00:12:06.596 --> 00:12:06.976
flow.

00:12:08.536 --> 00:12:09.656
Our next winner captures the

00:12:09.656 --> 00:12:11.316
essence of this experience in

00:12:11.316 --> 00:12:12.076
digital form.

00:12:13.026 --> 00:12:15.296
Please help me congratulate Flow

00:12:15.416 --> 00:12:15.976
by Moleskine.

00:12:16.516 --> 00:12:21.166
[ Applause ]

00:12:21.666 --> 00:12:22.226
>> Thanks, Dave.

00:12:23.536 --> 00:12:25.106
This demo was really hard to

00:12:25.236 --> 00:12:25.996
prepare.

00:12:26.106 --> 00:12:27.696
Every time I would launch Flow,

00:12:27.696 --> 00:12:28.696
and try to figure out what I

00:12:28.696 --> 00:12:30.196
would share with you today, I

00:12:30.196 --> 00:12:31.426
would start drawing, and

00:12:31.426 --> 00:12:32.936
completely lose track of what I

00:12:32.936 --> 00:12:34.816
was supposed to be doing, which

00:12:34.816 --> 00:12:36.606
is a testament, I think, to how

00:12:36.606 --> 00:12:38.236
well this app is designed.

00:12:38.986 --> 00:12:41.066
Now, to help you to get into and

00:12:41.136 --> 00:12:42.516
stay in a state of creative

00:12:42.516 --> 00:12:44.026
flow, they encourage you to set

00:12:44.026 --> 00:12:46.366
up everything in advance, like

00:12:46.456 --> 00:12:48.406
picking the color of the paper,

00:12:48.616 --> 00:12:50.016
or the patterns that you want to

00:12:50.016 --> 00:12:50.316
use.

00:12:51.216 --> 00:12:52.496
They also encourage you to set

00:12:52.496 --> 00:12:53.826
up the drawing tools in advance,

00:12:53.826 --> 00:12:55.516
so you're not messing around

00:12:55.516 --> 00:12:57.276
with interface later, and they

00:12:57.276 --> 00:12:58.766
have some really great drawing

00:12:58.806 --> 00:13:00.036
tools, like this mechanical

00:13:00.126 --> 00:13:00.526
pencil.

00:13:01.406 --> 00:13:02.546
Now, as you can see here,

00:13:02.966 --> 00:13:04.866
drawing is very realistic, and

00:13:04.866 --> 00:13:06.516
by supporting Apple Pencil 2

00:13:06.516 --> 00:13:09.286
gestures, iOS drawing APIs, and

00:13:09.286 --> 00:13:11.186
Metal, you can get some really

00:13:11.186 --> 00:13:12.746
realistic shading effects.

00:13:14.036 --> 00:13:15.136
It looks pretty true-to-life.

00:13:16.116 --> 00:13:17.886
They have a great felt-tip pen

00:13:18.226 --> 00:13:20.136
that looks basically like you

00:13:20.136 --> 00:13:22.266
would expect a pen to look, and

00:13:22.366 --> 00:13:24.876
they have great markers with

00:13:24.876 --> 00:13:27.486
really nice buildup of ink for

00:13:27.486 --> 00:13:29.736
realistic marker-like

00:13:29.786 --> 00:13:30.456
experience.

00:13:31.366 --> 00:13:32.656
They also have an awesome

00:13:32.656 --> 00:13:33.666
calligraphy pen.

00:13:34.256 --> 00:13:35.986
Now, playing with these tools --

00:13:36.506 --> 00:13:37.606
it kind of -- it takes me back

00:13:38.006 --> 00:13:39.036
to when I was a kid.

00:13:39.586 --> 00:13:41.146
My mom -- she was a really great

00:13:41.146 --> 00:13:42.856
calligrapher, and she had a

00:13:42.896 --> 00:13:44.216
business called Inklings.

00:13:44.796 --> 00:13:46.146
And -- yeah, I thought that was

00:13:46.146 --> 00:13:47.516
a pretty clever name, by the

00:13:47.516 --> 00:13:47.746
way.

00:13:48.546 --> 00:13:49.846
And when she would get supplies

00:13:49.846 --> 00:13:51.386
for her business, she would

00:13:51.386 --> 00:13:53.266
often take me with her, and I

00:13:53.266 --> 00:13:54.946
would have so much fun just

00:13:55.416 --> 00:13:57.156
playing with all of the markers

00:13:57.296 --> 00:13:57.956
and pens.

00:13:58.786 --> 00:14:00.426
Drawing tools here really kind

00:14:00.426 --> 00:14:01.996
of takes me back to that

00:14:01.996 --> 00:14:04.816
experience, but the real heart

00:14:04.816 --> 00:14:06.706
of the interface here is

00:14:06.706 --> 00:14:08.536
customizing the drawing tools.

00:14:09.286 --> 00:14:10.866
Everything in this interface is

00:14:10.866 --> 00:14:12.336
animated, and they even have

00:14:12.436 --> 00:14:13.656
these really great optional

00:14:13.716 --> 00:14:14.436
sound effects.

00:14:15.116 --> 00:14:16.126
Check out when you change the

00:14:16.126 --> 00:14:18.546
brush size, how the nibs change

00:14:18.546 --> 00:14:20.696
in response, or when you change

00:14:20.696 --> 00:14:23.386
the nibs, they pop on and pop

00:14:23.386 --> 00:14:23.736
off.

00:14:24.866 --> 00:14:26.086
But the heart of this interface

00:14:26.086 --> 00:14:27.256
is changing the color.

00:14:27.676 --> 00:14:29.636
You adjust the value on the side

00:14:29.636 --> 00:14:31.896
here on the right, swipe side to

00:14:31.996 --> 00:14:34.506
side to adjust saturation, and

00:14:34.506 --> 00:14:36.646
color by just spinning the color

00:14:36.646 --> 00:14:37.056
wheel.

00:14:37.926 --> 00:14:39.926
And check out how all of these

00:14:40.266 --> 00:14:41.646
-- all of these colors have

00:14:41.746 --> 00:14:42.706
unique names.

00:14:43.256 --> 00:14:45.166
There's 1400 names in all.

00:14:45.166 --> 00:14:46.876
It's just like a real marker

00:14:46.876 --> 00:14:47.226
set.

00:14:48.216 --> 00:14:50.166
Now, I'm feeling inspired to

00:14:50.166 --> 00:14:52.356
actually draw something, so to

00:14:52.356 --> 00:14:54.236
extend the canvas and stay in a

00:14:54.236 --> 00:14:56.276
state of flow, I just swipe over

00:14:56.276 --> 00:14:56.946
to the side.

00:14:57.766 --> 00:14:59.256
I'll draw something in the theme

00:14:59.256 --> 00:15:01.236
of calligraphy in front of a

00:15:01.236 --> 00:15:02.446
couple thousand people, so

00:15:02.446 --> 00:15:03.596
hopefully I do this all right.

00:15:03.596 --> 00:15:05.596
I'm going to draw a little

00:15:05.596 --> 00:15:06.186
feather pen.

00:15:07.046 --> 00:15:08.116
So I'm just going to trace in

00:15:08.116 --> 00:15:09.886
the outline with a felt-tip

00:15:09.886 --> 00:15:10.376
marker.

00:15:11.116 --> 00:15:14.846
It's looking pretty good.

00:15:15.696 --> 00:15:18.136
It's a little bit flat, so I

00:15:18.246 --> 00:15:20.886
think I'm going to add in some

00:15:20.886 --> 00:15:21.676
shading.

00:15:22.416 --> 00:15:25.386
It's a little bit more

00:15:25.386 --> 00:15:25.786
realistic.

00:15:25.786 --> 00:15:29.616
And then zoom in here -- whoops

00:15:30.356 --> 00:15:34.876
-- add in some color for the

00:15:34.876 --> 00:15:36.976
feather pen, and then touch

00:15:37.026 --> 00:15:38.976
things up with the eraser.

00:15:40.426 --> 00:15:40.756
All right.

00:15:41.286 --> 00:15:43.206
That's looking pretty good, but,

00:15:43.206 --> 00:15:45.636
you know, no drawing is complete

00:15:45.816 --> 00:15:47.576
until you sign your name.

00:15:48.236 --> 00:15:52.946
All right.

00:15:53.216 --> 00:15:55.176
I think we're done.

